#### **ISSUE 13: gs-1-11 "Real Love Baby" — Hammer-on description is contradictory**

**Exercise ID:** gs-1-11
**Location:** `level-01-first-sounds.js`, line 281

**Problematic text:**
> `"Add a hammer-on embellishment to the D chord: strum D, then hammer your middle finger onto the high E string 2nd fret (from the open string)."`

**What's wrong:** The standard D chord (xx0232) already has the middle finger on the high E string 2nd fret. The text says to "hammer your middle finger onto the high E string 2nd fret (from the open string)" -- but if the D chord is already fretted, the middle finger is already there. You can't hammer ON to a note you're already holding.

Looking at the D fingering from gs-1-3: "D: index on G string fret 2, ring on B string fret 3, middle on high E string fret 2." So the middle finger IS already on high E fret 2. The hammer-on doesn't make sense as described.

The intended embellishment is likely: lift the middle finger off the high E string (letting it ring open), then hammer back on to fret 2. This is a pull-off then hammer-on sequence. Or: use the pinky to hammer on to fret 3 of the high E string (which would be Dsus4 embellishment). The `wrong` field actually references "if it mutes the string, make sure your other fingers aren't shifting when you add the pinky" -- confirming a pinky hammer-on was intended.

