- **Correct advice**: The standard Gm7 barre chord based on the Em7 shape at fret 3 is **353363** (3-5-3-3-6-3) -- no, let me reconsider. The Em shape at fret 3 would be a Gm. The Em7 shape (020000) moved to fret 3 gives 3x3333 -- that's not standard. The standard Gm7 barre is typically the Am7 shape at fret 10, or the Em shape variant. The tab 353333 (with the text describing fret 5 on strings 5 and 4) has an internal inconsistency. The fingering description produces **355333**, not 353333. The exercise text should be reconciled -- likely the correct tab is **353333** and the finger description should say "ring finger at fret 5 on the 5th string" only (not also putting a finger on the 4th string at fret 5).

